{
  "1115432": "brace-expansion via exceljs->archiver->readdir-glob (GHSA-f886-m6hf-6m8v). exceljs@4.4.0 is the latest version and has not yet updated its archiver dependency. Attack vector requires controlling internal archiver glob patterns which is not possible in our Lambda environment. Remove once exceljs releases a fix.",
  "1116970": "uuid < 14.0.0 via exceljs (GHSA-w5hq-g745-h8pq). Fix requires downgrading to exceljs@3.4.0 which is a breaking change. The buf parameter code path that triggers the bounds issue is not exercised in our Lambda workload. Remove once exceljs updates its uuid dependency.",
  "1117868": "fast-xml-builder attribute quote bypass (GHSA-5wm8-gmm8-39j9) via @aws-sdk/xml-builder->fast-xml-parser->fast-xml-builder@1.1.5. Fix is in fast-xml-builder@1.1.7+ but @aws-sdk/xml-builder@3.972.22 (latest) has not yet updated to fast-xml-parser@5.7.3. Attack vector requires controlling XML attribute values passed to the builder; the AWS SDK controls these inputs internally. Remove once AWS SDK updates its fast-xml-parser dependency.",
  "1117869": "fast-xml-builder comment value regex bypass (GHSA-45c6-75p6-83cc) via @aws-sdk/xml-builder->fast-xml-parser->fast-xml-builder@1.1.5. Same dependency chain and upstream fix status as 1117868. Remove once AWS SDK updates its fast-xml-parser dependency."
}
